%% Reviewed 2026-04-17 for v0.1.11 to show Delivery Intelligence handing compact packet, execution, memory, Tribunal, visible intervention, and benchmark proof through one closed loop.
sequenceDiagram
  participant Dev as Developer or AI Coding Engine
  participant Repo as Repo + Plans + Specs
  participant Gates as Local Gates + CI
  participant Compass as Compass Timeline
  participant Odylith as Odylith Observer
  participant Delivery as Delivery Intelligence
  participant Context as Context Engine
  participant Execution as Execution Engine
  participant Tribunal as Tribunal
  participant Remediator as Remediator
  participant Visibility as Visible Intervention Broker
  participant Benchmark as Benchmark Harness
  participant Runtime as Runtime v4 Store
  participant Operator as Maintainer
  participant Shell as Tooling Shell
  participant Evidence as Radar / Registry / Atlas / Compass

  Dev->>Repo: Edit code, contracts, plans, generators
  Repo-->>Odylith: Changed paths and worktree signal
  Gates->>Odylith: Test, build, policy, release outcomes
  Compass->>Odylith: Decision, implementation, clearance events

  Odylith->>Odylith: Observe and fingerprint
  alt No meaningful case delta
    Odylith->>Odylith: Reuse cached posture and back off toward 300s idle cadence
  else Case fingerprint changed or leverage rises
    Odylith->>Delivery: Build or refresh scoped dossiers
    Delivery-->>Odylith: Ranked candidate cases + evidence bundles
    Delivery->>Context: Build compact packet digest
    Context-->>Delivery: Packet quality, target resolution, route readiness
    Delivery->>Execution: Build compact execution snapshot
    Execution-->>Delivery: Admissibility, mode, next move, closure, validation
    alt Persisted reasoning artifact exists
      Odylith->>Tribunal: Reuse cached cases or run selective actor pass on contested or high-value cases
      Tribunal-->>Odylith: Briefs, outcomes, systemic themes, confidence
    else Reasoning artifact missing during refresh
      Odylith->>Tribunal: Build deterministic-only fallback cases locally
      Tribunal-->>Odylith: Deterministic case_queue plus systemic context
    end
    Odylith->>Remediator: Compile bounded correction packet when prescription is executable
    Remediator-->>Odylith: Deterministic, AI engine, hybrid, or manual packet
    Tribunal->>Visibility: Emit compact user-visible risk signal when earned
    Visibility-->>Shell: Render Observation / Proposal / Assist only when visible proof policy allows
    Execution->>Benchmark: Record execution posture and false-admit or false-deny evidence
    Odylith->>Runtime: Persist delivery_intelligence.v4, reasoning.v4, posture.v4
  end

  Odylith-->>Shell: Refresh compact inbox preview
  Odylith-->>Operator: Show case brief, proof, and next action
  Evidence-->>Operator: Provide native workstream, component, diagram, and timeline context

  alt Packet requires approval
    Operator->>Odylith: Approve packet
    alt Deterministic packet
      Odylith->>Remediator: Execute bounded commands
      Remediator-->>Odylith: Validation, rollback safety, execution result
      Remediator->>Benchmark: Record closure and validation proof
    else AI-engine or hybrid packet
      Odylith->>Remediator: Emit constrained handoff payload
      Remediator-->>Operator: Send to AI engine
    end
    Operator->>Odylith: Record clearance after post-action checks pass
    Odylith->>Compass: Append approval and clearance evidence
  else Manual review only
    Operator->>Evidence: Perform discriminating check and decide
  end

  Note over Context,Visibility: Hot lanes consume compact packet, execution, memory, Tribunal, and delivery-ledger summaries only.<br/>No provider call or repo-wide scan belongs inside visibility or status checks.
